OL,3,CBlue Islands customers left camping
OL,4,Covernight in Guernsey airport
OL,6,FWith nowhere to stay at short-notice,
OL,7,FGuernsey Ports contacted Guernsey
OL,8,FCivil Protection, who arranged for air
OL,9,Fmattresses and sleeping bags to be
OL,10,Fbrought.
OL,12,FThe Landside Cafe was opened earlier
OL,13,Fthan usual on Sunday morning so that
OL,14,Fpassengers could have hot drinks and
OL,15,Ffood.
OL,17,FGuernsey Ports Chief Operating Officer
OL,18,FRoss Coppolo said: "I would like to
OL,19,Fthank our teamsJand the Civil
OL,20,FProtection volunteers for their hard
OL,21,Fwork late on Saturday night.
